          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## ExpressRoute Troubleshooting Guide\n\n### BGP Availability < 100%\n| Symptom | Possible Cause | Action |\n|---------|----------------|--------|\n| BGP drops to 0% | Provider circuit down | Contact provider, check Service Health |\n| BGP intermittent | Flapping BGP session | Check route table size, verify BGP timers |\n| BGP low but not 0% | Partial connectivity | Check primary/secondary path status |\n\n### ARP Availability < 100%\n| Symptom | Possible Cause | Action |\n|---------|----------------|--------|\n| ARP at 0% | Layer 2 connectivity lost | Check physical connection, VLAN config |\n| ARP intermittent | MAC address issues | Verify peering configuration |\n\n### High Bandwidth Utilization\n| Threshold | Severity | Action |\n|-----------|----------|--------|\n| > 70% | Warning | Monitor for trends, plan capacity |\n| > 80% | Alert | Prepare bandwidth upgrade |\n| > 95% | Critical | Immediate capacity upgrade required |\n\n### Packet Drops\n| Symptom | Possible Cause | Action |\n|---------|----------------|--------|\n| Consistent drops | Bandwidth exceeded | Increase circuit capacity |\n| Burst drops | Traffic spikes | Implement QoS policies |\n| Random drops | Network issues | Check for errors in provider network |\n\n### Useful Links\n- [Azure Portal - ExpressRoute](https://portal.azure.com/#blade/HubsExtension/BrowseResource/resourceType/Microsoft.Network%2FexpressRouteCircuits)\n- [Azure Service Health](https://portal.azure.com/#blade/Microsoft_Azure_Health/AzureHealthBrowseBlade)\n- [ExpressRoute Documentation](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/expressroute/)",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "Troubleshooting Reference",
      "type": "text"
